properties.location: 21600 block of 29th Ave. S., Des Moines
properties.suspect: Ronald H. Mitchell (aka David Michael Long)
properties.details: Brown was fatally shot in the chest. His body was discovered in an abandoned house frequented by drug users. Ronald "Shorty" Mitchell, 45, was charged with second-degree murder in October. Prosecutors say the two men had argued and Mitchell left but returned and shot Brown. Mitchell was under the supervision of the state Department of Corrections at the time.

properties.location: 10900 block of S.E. 254th Place S., Kent
properties.cause_of_death: gunshot wounds to head and chest
properties.arrest_date: charged 3/23/16
properties.details: Young was with a friend when a gunman opened fire on them from a Cadillac, hitting Young in the head and chest. Anthony J. Smith, 17, was arrested hours later in SeaTac on unrelated firearm and drug charges. Smith, who was charged with first-degree murder in March, wanted to kill rival gang members as part of an ongoing feud between two gangs, prosecutors said.

Zavala, a student at Highline High School, was shot in the head in the parking lot of a Burien apartment complex. A car was seen speeding off and a group of people left the scene on foot. No one has been arrested in connection with Zavala’s death. Five days after his killing, a 36-year-old man was wounded in a shooting in the same parking lot.

properties.location: 5th Ave. S. and S. Jackson St., Seattle
properties.details: Cross, a clerk at the Union Station Market, was stabbed to death when he grabbed the collar of a customer and tried to shove the man out of the store. During the altercation, David Allen Moore, 50, allegedly stabbed Cross at least three times. He was identified from DNA on a travel mug left behind in the store. Moore was charged with second-degree murder, with a deadly weapon enhancement.

properties.cause_of_death: both died from multiple head injuries/blunt force trauma
properties.details: Sippach was visiting Humphrey in Humphrey's apartment at Bell Tower, a Seattle Housing Authority building in Belltown. According to police, the bodies had been in the apartment for more than a few days before they were discovered. Both men died from multiple blunt-force injuries to the head. There have been no arrests.

properties.location: 1500 block of Airport Way S., Seattle
properties.cause_of_death: both died from multiple gunshot wounds
properties.suspect: James Taafulisia     Jerome Taafulisia        Joseph Taafulisia
properties.arrest_date: All three arrested 2/1/16
properties.details: Zapata and Tran were fatally shot and three other people were wounded in The Jungle homeless encampment during an apparent drug rip-off. The suspected shooters are brothers James and Jerome Taafulisia, now 18 and 17, who were charged as adults while their now-14-year-old brother was charged as a juvenile with two counts of second-degree murder and three counts of first-degree assault.

properties.location: S. Garden St. and Rainier Ave. S., Seattle
properties.details: Hilts and two other men were shot at the Shell gas station on Rainier Avenue South, just north of South Othello Street. Hilts died at the scene; the other victims, ages 47 and 50, were hospitalized with serious injuries. Seattle police said at the time they believe the three men were targeted. There have not been any arrests.

According to prosecutors, Gennings was allegedly set up by a friend, Michael Rogers, now 17, to be robbed of marijuana and cash. Rogers’ co-defendant, Diante Pellum, now 15, is accused of shooting Gennings once in the back of the head while Gennings sat in the driver’s seat of his car outside a Taco Bell restaurant. Both have been charged with first-degree murder and will be prosecuted as adults.

properties.cause_of_death: bleeding in the brain due to blunt force injury to the head with neglect as a primary contributor to death
properties.arrest_date: Parents arrested 11/3/16; each charged with second-degree murder on 11/4/16
properties.details: Demond Hudson, 27, and BJ Meaola Silipa, 26, took their dead 6-month-old boy to St. Francis Hospital in Federal Way, where hospital staff called police after finding the baby had suffered numerous injuries and appeared malnourished. An autopsy determined "DJ" had 21 rib fractures of varying ages, a newly broken right arm, a possible skull fracture and other injuries. In November, the parents were each charged with second-degree murder.

Fountain was stabbed to death when he tried to break up a fight between his mother and her boyfriend, Fritz Karl Ratcliffe, now 27, according to prosecutors. The couple had been dating for six months and Ratcliffe had moved in two months before Fountain was killed. Police say Ratcliffe fled but was arrested in Anacortes. He is charged with second-degree murder domestic violence.

properties.location: S.W. 100th St. and 9th Ave. S.W., White Center
properties.details: Nickerson's body was found in the roadway. He moved to the Seattle area from Mississippi in 2013. No one has been arrested in his death.

Seattle police were conducting surveillance outside a suspected drug house when they saw Taylor, a known felon, arrive and spotted him wearing a holstered handgun. The officers called for backup and say he reached for a gun when they tried to take him into custody. He was shot by two officers and later died at Harborview Medical Center, where medical personnel found six ounces of crack and black-tar heroin in a bag around his neck.

properties.location: 3300 block of S. Holly St., Seattle
properties.details: Gondo's body was found slumped over the steering wheel of his car on Feb. 24, but the medical examiner’s office determined he had died a day earlier. Maryanne Atkins, then 16, is accused of shooting Gondo in the right temple with a gun Gondo kept under the front passenger seat. Atkins, who was charged as an adult with first-degree murder, allegedly killed Gondo to rob him of $3,000 cash.

properties.cause_of_death: injuries resulting from assault (complications from a broken hip)
properties.details: Nesbitt was shopping at a QFC supermarket when Brandon Benevides is accused of violently shoving a grocery cart into him, causing him to fall and break a hip on Feb. 29. Prosecutors say the incident was unprovoked and part of a disturbing escalation in Benevides’ erratic, violent behavior. Nesbitt died from complications of his injuries in April. Benevides, 34, was charged 10 days later with second-degree manslaughter.

properties.location: 2400 block of Auburn Way S., Auburn
properties.arrest_date: arrested 3/2/16   charged 4/4/16
properties.details: Partman was on a sidewalk outside the Muckleshoot Casino when she was struck by an out-of-control SUV driven by Russell Duane Ward, 35. Ward was wanted on a Department of Corrections warrant and allegedly thought an Auburn patrol officer, who was responding to a burglary call, was trying to pull him over. Ward was charged with second-degree murder.

properties.location: 11000 block of 8th Ave. S., Boulevard Park
properties.cause_of_death: gunshot wound to chest and face
properties.details: Blacktongue walked into a 7-Eleven and attacked a customer and clerk with a hatchet, according to the King County Sheriff’s Office. The customer, who had a concealed-pistol license, fatally shot Blacktongue. The clerk suffered a minor wound to the abdomen. In September, prosecutors declined to file charges, concluding the customer, a 60-year-old Seattle man, used lawful force in shooting Blacktongue and was defending the clerk from further injury or death.

Flowers had previously dated a woman who was dating Brandon Green, now 33. Flowers and his former girlfriend were at another woman’s apartment when Green banged on the door but wasn’t allowed in, prosecutors say. He allegedly got a gun from his car, forced his way into the apartment and shot Flowers in the chest. The woman who lived in the apartment then shot Green, who survived. He was charged with second-degree murder.

properties.cause_of_death: brain damage as a result of asphyxia -- strangulation
properties.details: A neighbor called 911 on March 20 and Seattle police officers forced their way into Straalsund's apartment, where they found Casey Stanley Henderson, now 22, choking Straalsund, who had severe head and facial injuries. Officers performed CPR but she never regained consciousness and died two days later. Henderson is charged with first-degree murder domestic violence. Both were University of Washington students and had casually dated for about six months.

properties.arrest_date: NOT ARRESTED
properties.details: Seattle police were called to a domestic disturbance and found Lampkin in his parked car in an alley outside his girlfriend’s apartment. The girlfriend, who was six months pregnant at the time, had fled but was interviewed by police a few days later. Lampkin died from a stab wound to his chest. His girlfriend has not been charged.

properties.location: 430 block of Bremerton Ave. N.E., Renton
properties.arrest_date: arrested in Yakima County 3/30/16  charged in King County 4/7/16
properties.details: Al-Samarrai's body was found in the stairwell of an apartment complex. Omar "Flacco" Acevedo, a member of a street gang, had some kind of ongoing disagreement with Al-Samarrai. While hanging out with mutual friends at a Renton apartment, they argued, then took their dispute outside, where Al-Samarrai was shot once in the head. Acevedo was later arrested in Yakima for allegedly robbing a man at gunpoint, stealing his car and leading deputies on a high-speed pursuit. He was charged in April with second-degree murder in connection with Al-Samarrai’s death.

properties.cause_of_death: multiple gunshot wounds (Purvis shot twice in the chest; Whitmore shot four times, including twice in the head)
properties.arrest_date: $5M arrest warrant issued and Lipsey charged with two counts of first-degree murder on 11/10/16. Arrested in Federal Way on 12/5/16.
properties.details: Whitmore had apparently threatened to shoot Darion Lipsey, which enraged Lipsey, according to prosecutors. Lipsey, 22, and a woman drove around downtown Seattle until they spotted Whitmore and Purvis on Second Avenue Extension South. Lipsey jumped out of the car and confronted Whitmore, police say. While Whitmore was the intended target, Purvis apparently moved into the line of fire and both he and Whitmore were killed. Charged with two counts of first-degree murder, Lipsey was arrested in Federal Way in December.

Berry was found on a South Seattle sidewalk with multiple gunshot wounds and was pronounced dead at Harborview. He apparently moved here from Louisiana after Hurricane Katrina. He died less than 24 hours after posting bail on an unrelated firearms charge. No arrests have been made.

properties.location: 4000 block of S. 340th St., near Auburn
properties.details: Ianniciello's wife and daughter returned home and found him dead in bed with a gunshot wound to the head. Ianniciello owned a produce distribution company in Kent. No arrests have been made.

McLaren was found shot to death in the parking lot at The Cove Apartment Homes. Police believe his death was retaliation for the fatal self-defense shooting of Dylan Lee Oman, 18, in Tacoma in January 2016. McLaren’s death is one of four which Federal Way police have attributed to a suspect who is in jail on unrelated charges but has not been charged in any of the killings.

properties.location: 1900 block of Camus Ave. N.E., Renton
properties.arrest_date: arrested 4/11/16 in Lake Stevens
properties.details: Lyne had dated John Robert Charlton, now 38, for about a month and attended a Mariners game with him on April 8. The next day, Lyne’s ex-husband reported her missing and found she’d left her purse and cellphone in her house. Over the next nine days, Seattle police found her dismembered remains in three different locations. Charlton was arrested April 11 in Lake Stevens. Prosecutors say he strangled Lyne in her home, then dismembered her with a saw in her bathtub. He is charged with first-degree murder.

Several people called 911 to report hearing multiple gunshots and when police responded, DiTullio allegedly led officers on a five-mile pursuit before getting stuck in the driveway of a house on 21st Avenue Southwest. As officers yelled commands, one saw the door to the vehicle swing open and spotted DiTullio pointing an assault-style rifle at the officers. One officer fired multiple shots, killing DiTullio, who had a rifle on his lap.

properties.arrest_date: arrested 5/4/16   charged 5/9/16
properties.details: Voegele was shot in the face in the breezeway of a Burien apartment building, allegedly by Gianni Cunningham, 17. According to charging papers, Cunningham claimed he was the intended target of a drive-by shooting but a resident at the apartment complex told police he’d seen, through his peephole, Cunningham playing with a 9-mm handgun. The resident also heard Voegele repeatedly tell Cunningham to put the gun away, then witnessed her getting shot. Cunningham has been charged with second-degree murder.

properties.location: 22800 block of 30th Ave. S., Des Moines
properties.arrest_date: arrested at his house on 5/9
properties.case: 16-8-00582-1 SEA King County prosecutors seeking decline to adult court
properties.details: Phelps, who was visiting friends, was shot in the parking lot of a Burien apartment complex and died at Harborview. He was allegedly killed by a 14-year-old, who has been charged with second-degree murder, possession of a stolen firearm and burglary. Prosecutors are seeking to try the juvenile as an adult.

properties.arrest_date: Warrant issued and a first-degree murder charge was filed on 1/11/17; Galeana-Madrigal in the wind as of 1/11/17
properties.details: A no-bail warrant was issued in Jan. 2017 for the arrest of Juan Felipe Galeana-Madrigal, who was charged with first-degree murder in connection with Mendoza's death. According to prosecutors, Galeana-Madrigal shot Mendoza twice in the head because he believed Mendoza was an informant in a federal narcotics investigation. Mendoza, who apparently owed Galeana-Madrigal money, was an alleged drug distributor who sold heroin and meth.

properties.location: 1300 block of S.W. Campus Dr., Federal Way
properties.details: Kelley, a Seattle resident, was smoking on the porch of a friend’s apartment in Federal Way when he was shot once in the back. His death is one of four that Federal Way police have attributed to a known suspect who is in custody on unrelated charges but has not been charged in connection with any of the fatal shootings.

properties.location: 2200 block of S. 333rd St., Federal Way
properties.details: Cohens, a Tacoma resident and the father of two young children, was found slumped over the wheel of his car. Federal Way police say there is evidence that drug activity was connected to his death. His death is one of four that Federal Way police have attributed to a known suspect who is in custody on unrelated charges but has not been charged in connection with any of the fatal shootings.

properties.location: 1800 block of S.W. 356th St., Federal Way
properties.details: Gutierrez was out running with his dog when he was shot and found dead on a sidewalk. A University of Washington graduate and Navy veteran, he had been training for a marathon. His death is one of four that Federal Way police have attributed to a known suspect who is in custody on unrelated charges but has not been charged in connection with any of the fatal shootings.

Officers responded to a report of a fight and found Garnica lying in the street. He died at the scene. Police believe his killing is likely gang-related. No one has been arrested in connection with his death.

properties.suspect: 94-year-old man questioned by SPD; he was not arrested. Vic taken to HMC, where he died on 6/2/16
properties.details: Webb was shot in the chest and was found lying outside a home. He died at Harborview. Seattle police interviewed his 94-year-old neighbor about the shooting but have made no arrests.

properties.arrest_date: arrested at her parents' house on 6/4/16  charged 6/8/16
properties.details: Tami A. Christianson was charged with second-degree murder, accused of killing her 15-month-old son in her parents' house near Redmond. Christianson, who has a history of mental illness and prescription-drug abuse, had apparently made comments about killing Brody and putting him up for adoption. According to charging documents, Brody's father and grandparents had tried to protect the child from his mother.

properties.cause_of_death: bacterial infection with abcess of the back, chest wall and lung, with malnutrition, rib fractures and pulmonary lacerations as contributors
properties.suspect: Mariah L. Phillips            Lee M. Dupay
properties.arrest_date: the baby's parents were arrested 6/24/16; charged 6/28/16
properties.details: Mariah Phillips, 25, and Lee Dupay, 34, are each charged with second-degree murder domestic violence in connection with the death of their baby girl. Charging papers say the baby died from abuse and neglect, had numerous rib fractures and was severely malnourished. The couple's other children, twin 2-year-old girls, were placed with Child Protective Services.

properties.location: 5th Ave. S. and S. Jackson St., Seattle
properties.cause_of_death: cerebral contusions and subdermal hematoma due to blunt force injury to the head
properties.arrest_date: Gomez was arrested 6/30/16; charged 7/1/16 with first-degree manslaughter
properties.details: Arbo was involved in a fight on May 2, when he was assaulted and knocked to the ground, smashing his head on a metal newspaper box. He died June 26 at Harborview. Antonio David Gomez, 32, has been charged with first-degree manslaughter.

Dacanay’s body was found by police in a stolen car in the parking lot of a SeaTac apartment complex on July 6. The medical examiner determined he died July 4 from multiple gunshot wounds. No arrests have been made.

properties.arrest_date: Mullins and Gregg were arrested 7/8/16 in Montesano following a traffic stop for speeding. Charged 7/13/16
properties.details: Clayton was ambushed inside the trailer he shared with his father and was killed with guns stolen from his father’s locked gun safe. The trailer was then set ablaze. Dylan Scott Mullins, now 19, and Sebastian Gregg, now 18, were arrested in Montesano, Grays Harbor County, two days later when a trooper pulled them over in a stolen pickup. Police say both admitted to killing Clayton because Clayton had previously beat up Mullins. Mullins and Gregg are each charged with first-degree murder, first-degree arson and first-degree burglary.

Both Smith and Travis Pendley, now 31, were transients who were camping at Fenster Park on the Green River. Pendley allegedly accused Smith of stealing tools from his campsite and in a confrontation, fatally shot Smith, whose body was found in the woods by passersby the next day. Pendley was charged with second-degree murder, theft of a firearm and unlawful possession of a firearm.

properties.arrest_date: Arrested 8/11 on unrelated warrants; charged with second-degree murder on 8/30/16.
properties.details: Khamphouvong pulled his SUV into the driveway of a house in the 9300 block of 39th Avenue South and was immediately blocked in by another vehicle, whose occupants allegedly ordered him out of his SUV. Instead, Khamphouvong quickly reversed, slamming into the other vehicle as Kenny Am, now 21, opened fire, killing Khamphouvong. Seattle police say Am killed Khamphouvong in apparent retaliation for stealing a machine that makes fake credit cards. Am was charged with second-degree murder.

properties.location: 2800 block of E. Arthur Place, Seattle
properties.details: A passer-by called 911 after spotting Bolar's body just inside the doorway of her Madison Valley house. Bolar died from multiple gunshot wounds. There have been no arrests in connection with her death.

Martelli was apparently angry at his neighbor for borrowing tools and refusing to give them back. He allegedly fired a shotgun into his neighbor's car, injuring the man, who then attempted to drive to the police station but crashed before he got there. Police responded to Martelli's apartment, where Martelli fired at least once at officers. Two officers returned fire, killing the mentally ill man.

Campos, a transient woman living in a homeless encampment off 88th Avenue South, died of multiple gunshot wounds. Less than 24 hours later, a homeless man was fatally shot at the same encampment. There have been no arrests.
Dias, who lived in the same homeless encampment as Louisa Campos, was fatally shot less than 24 hours after she was gunned down and killed. There have been no arrests.

properties.arrest_date: arrested 9/14/16 in Hayden, Idaho; charged 9/15/16 with first-degree murder, first-degree assault and first degree UPFA. Booked into the RJC on 9/16/16
properties.details: Police say Dominguez-Navarro was fatally shot and a 23-year-old man was gravely wounded in an apparent drug rip-off over $1,200 worth of marijuana. The men were shot as they sat in a car parked at a Tukwila apartment complex. Treston Baladez-Castillo, 20, was arrested in Hayden, Idaho, in September and is charged with first-degree murder, first-degree assault and first-degree unlawful possession of a firearm.

properties.location: 2500 block of S. 286th Place, Federal Way
properties.details: Barber was found dead at an apartment complex in Federal Way and police searched for two men in their 20s, possibly driving a white Chevrolet Malibu. Responding officers were surrounded by a group of 50 to 75 people, but no witnesses came forward. No arrests have been made.
Nein was shot to death and found in between buildings in a couple of apartment complexes in Kent. No one has been arrested in connection with Nein’s homicide.

Love was a construction worker from Oregon who was staying at the Motel 6 with two co-workers while working a local job. He got into an argument with suspect Rodney C. Wheeler, 39, who police say was baiting Love and a co-worker to fight and using racial slurs. Love was fatally shot in the chest in the motel parking lot. A second man, also a guest at the motel, was shot in the back by a stray bullet as he got out of the shower. Wheeler was arrested in October and charged with second-degree murder, second-degree assault and second-degree unlawful possession of a firearm.

properties.arrest_date: arrested at the scene on 9/4/16; charged w/ first-degree murder and first-degree assault on 9/9/16. Both charges also carry FA enhancements.
properties.details: Huynh and suspect Quang Ngoc Dinh were friends who attended a small gathering at Huynh's girlfriend's house in Kent. Dinh became angry because Huynh wanted to go to bed instead of staying up to continue drinking with Dinh. After allegedly threatening Huynh and his girlfriend with a kitchen knife, Dinh is accused of retrieving a handgun from his car, then firing through an open door, killing Huynh and grazing a 31-year-old Kent woman. Dinh was charged with first-degree murder and first-degree assault.

properties.location: S 128th St and 21st Ave. S., Burien
properties.cause_of_death: multiple gunshot wounds to the chest
properties.details: Hovey and some friends attended a house party in Burien. Hovey left and a short time later his friends found him on the ground outside with three gunshot wounds to the chest. The friends got him in a car and drove him to Highline Medical Center; Hovey was then transferred to Harborview, where he died. No arrests have been made.

properties.location: 800 block of Pike St. N.E., Auburn
properties.agency: APD; Renton PD investigating the OIS
properties.details: Auburn police say a patrol officer responded to a vandalism call at an apartment complex and was with a citizen when Ell approached them, armed with a 3-foot long metal pipe. Police say Ell, who also had a knife sheathed on his belt, raised the pipe as if to swing it and ignored the officer's commands to drop it. The officer shot and killed Ell.

properties.location: 317000 block of 3rd Place S.W., Federal Way
properties.arrest_date: 9/24/16 to HMC; charged w/ first-degree murder on 9/28, though he has still not been booked into jail. Bail set at $5 million
properties.details: Apling and her estranged boyfriend, Rashied Mitchell, got into an argument inside Mitchell’s mother’s apartment when Apling went to pick up their children after she got off work. Mitchell, 46, is accused of shooting Apling in front of the children, then shooting himself in the head. Mitchell, who has a lengthy history of domestic-violence assaults, survived and was charged with first-degree murder.

properties.cause_of_death: perinatal asphixya due to maternal thermal burns
properties.suspect: The child's mother, Sandeep Kaur, set herself on fire in an apparent suicide attempt. The 34-year-old died at Harborview on 10/21/16 from thermal burns to 65 percent of her body and her death was ruled a suicide.
properties.details: Sandeep Kaur, a 34-year-old expectant mother, was very close to full term when she attempted suicide by setting herself on fire. She delivered her baby, who was dubbed Baby Boy Singh, but he lived less than three hours. His death was ruled a homicide. Kaur died a month later at Harborview.

properties.location: 32800 block of Hoyt Rd. S.W., Federal Way
properties.details: Sloboda apparently cut off a driver while driving to visit his wife and newborn at the hospital. He was chased by the other driver, so went to his brother's apartment in Federal Way, where he stayed for about an hour. After leaving his brother's home, Sloboda was found fatally shot in his car. No one has been arrested in connection with his death.

properties.location: Occidental Ave. S. & S. Washington St., Seattle
properties.details: Seattle police officers, who were in Pioneer Square at bar closing time, heard several gunshots and found Perry dead from a gunshot wound to the head in a parking lot at Occidental and Washington. No arrests have been made.

Gonclaves was stabbed by a stranger at the Tukwila-International Boulevard Link Light Rail station and died a short time later at Harborview. Based on witness descriptions, officers tracked down Mehmet Ali Whicker, 30, nearby. Police say he had blood on his hands and clothes. Whicker, who has an extensive criminal history in multiple states, was charged with second-degree murder.

properties.location: 24th Street and F. Street S.E., Auburn
properties.details: Auburn police say Valdez-Herrera was inside a vehicle when Alexander Joachin, then 16, fired numerous gunshots, killing him. Police say Joachin is a known gang member who told detectives he shot Valdez-Herrera because the 17-year-old had disrespected other gang members. Joachin was charged as an adult with second-degree murder.

Federal Way police responded to a domestic dispute between two adult brothers and arrived at a mobile-home park to find a number of family members had locked themselves in a room in a mobile home, fearing for their safety. They were helped out a window by officers. Ricardo Hernandez, 21, was armed with a butcher knife and is alleged to have told officers, "I don't have the guts to kill myself; you're going to have to do it for me." He was fatally shot by two officers.

properties.location: Airport Way S. and S. Bayview St., Seattle
properties.suspect: OFFICER INVOLVED SHOOTING: Sgt. Heidi Tuttle, South Precinct
properties.details: A Seattle police sergeant shot and killed Taylor after encountering a fight between Taylor and another man near the The Jungle homeless encampment as city crews and police were working to move people out of the camp. Taylor was armed with a knife and was apparently attacking the second man when he was shot. Police recovered a knife at the scene.

properties.location: 400 block of Jason Ave. N., Kent
properties.details: Kent police were serving a search warrant as part of a fraudulent-activity investigation and encountered Reddeck, who lived at the house and was armed with a handgun. Two detectives and a patrol officer fired at him; Reddeck later died at Harborview.

properties.location: 15800 block of S.E. 382nd Place, Muckleshoot Indian Reservation
properties.suspect: OFFICER INVOLVED SHOOTING: Deputies Nicholas Pritchett and Tim Lewis
properties.details: Davis, the mother of three young children who was five months pregnant with her fourth child, was despondent and apparently suicidal when her boyfriend contacted a deputy and asked him to conduct a welfare check on her. No one answered the door and two deputies entered the house, where they found Davis armed with a handgun. Both deputies fired, killing Davis. Deputies recovered two rifles and a loaded handgun from the bedroom where she was shot.

properties.cause_of_death: blunt force head injury and acute combined alcohol and methamphetamine intoxication
properties.details: Police were called to a fight among family members at a home in Kent and found Leuma unresponsive in the street outside. He died at the scene. Leuma died from a blunt-force injury to the head and acute combined alcohol and methamphetamine intoxication. There have been no arrests.

properties.location: 1300 block of Rainier Ave. S., Seattle
properties.details: Officers responded to reports of a shooting inside a vehicle and found Barber in the backseat. He died at the scene. Three other people were in the car and police identified Larry Edward Thomas Jr., a 23-year-old passenger, as the shooter. Police say he couldn't provide a reason, other than that he had taken PCP before the shooting. Thomas was charged with second-degree murder and second-degree unlawful possession of a firearm.

properties.location: 14500 block of Whitman Ave. N., Shoreline
properties.details: Frost and two alleged accomplices, Jacob Mezich and Andrew Carpenter, kicked down the door of a Shoreline condominium to steal drugs, believing the home was empty because the owner was in jail. Frost, who was armed with an AR-15 rifle, was shot and killed by the condo owner’s roommate. Mezich, 26, and Carpenter, 27, fled but were arrested a few days later and charged with first-degree burglary and attempted first-degree robbery. The man who killed Frost has not been charged with a crime.

properties.location: E. Olive Way and 13th Avenue, Seattle
properties.details: Witnesses told police that a gunman ran up to Osborn-Bash on the street early on Nov. 13th, shot him multiple times, then fled in a white SUV. The witnesses were unable to provide a detailed suspect description. Osborn-Bash died the next day at Harborview. No one has been arrested.

properties.arrest_date: 11/3/2016; charged with 2 counts of first-degree assault and first-degree UPFA on 11/8/16; charges amended to second-degree murder and attempted second-degree murder on 12/6/16
properties.details: On Nov. 2, Bacani and a 27-year-old man were outside a Shoreline home talking to Reuben Melegrito, a "social friend" who showed up unannounced. Melegrito, an admitted gang member, suddenly opened fire after a minor argument, police say. Bacani, who was shot twice, died Nov. 20 at Harborview. The 27-year-old was shot four times, but survived. Melegrito, 27, was arrested at his family’s home in Renton and charged with second-degree murder and attempted second-degree murder.

properties.location: Talbot Road S. and S. 21st St., Renton
properties.arrest_date: arrested 11/29/16; charged with second-degree murder, second-degree assault and first-degree UPFA on 12/2/16
properties.details: Sheikh was on a Metro bus in Renton on Nov. 29 and chatted with Faisal Adan, 22, an old acquaintance. Adan is accused of pulling out a revolver and shooting Sheikh for no apparent reason in front of numerous passengers, then threatening the bus driver with the gun as he demanded to be let off the bus. Adan was arrested a short time later and is charged with second-degree murder, second-degree assault and first-degree unlawful possession of a firearm. Sheikh died Dec. 1st at Harborview.

properties.location: 39th Ave. S. and S. Warsaw St., Seattle
properties.details: Nguyen, walking home after work, was attacked in an attempted purse snatching. She struggled with her assailant and was shot multiple times. He fled without her purse. Nguyen died a short time later at Harborview. No one has been arrested in connection with her killing.

Perez-Placencia was fatally shot by her ex-boyfriend, 24-year-old Erick Ortuno-Perez. He also shot another woman in the leg before fatally shooting himself. Perez-Placencia and Ortuno-Perez were parents of a 4-year-old daughter. Perez-Placencia had obtained a protection order against Ortuno-Perez, who police say was controlling, abusive and had previously threatened to kill her and himself.

properties.location: 32100 block of 46th Place S.W., Federal Way
properties.details: Hicks was attending a gathering at a Federal Way apartment complex and was shot during an argument, apparently over possible stolen property. He later died at Harborview. There have been no arrests in connection with his death.
